rk](https://github.com/DerekCresswell/glfw/tree/window-pos-hint).\r\n\r\nThis was just done with `window.c` so it should work will all platforms. This also allows for the default location of either X or Y to be applied if only one of the hints was given.  \r\nThere is the problem that for the first few frames (usually 4 main loops for me) the window would be in the default location. This creates an obvious jump.\r\n\r\nI have been trying (and will continue) to get rid of this initial jump. It would appear to me that this requires setting up this implementation in each `_glfwPlatformCreateWindow` function.  I'm on Ubuntu and was experimenting but could not seem to get X11 to respect the values I passed in during `XWindowCreate`, perhaps because of the defaults being set later during `_glfwPlatformShowWindow`.\r\n\r\nIf the changes I made on my fork seem acceptable I'll turn it into a PR. Otherwise I would not mind any ideas or guidance on how to remove the jitter. I'll continue looking into this for a little while longer.\r\n\r\nI'll also mention, I feel like adding this to `glfwCreateWindow` would be convenient, it might be getting to cluttered as a signature. Also forcing the user to chose a position could be awkward as  most of the time the window system chooses a specific position.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments/633345655/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"DerekCresswell","id":44453572,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0NDUzNTcy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/44453572?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/DerekCresswell","html_url":"https://github.com/DerekCresswell","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DerekCresswell/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DerekCresswell/following{/other_user}",